<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1024542>
    dc:description "Fig. 14. (A-E) Sertularella mediterranea Hartlaub, 1901. Colony fragments after Genzano (1990) (A) and Mediterranean material HRG- 0001 (B). Hydrothecae after Blanco [1967, as S. picta (Meyen, 1834)] (C), HRG- 0001 (D), and Mañé Garzón & Milstein (1973, as S. ruguayensis) (E). (F, G) Sertularella microtheca Leloup, 1974. Portion of erect stem (F) and hydrothecae (G) from HRG- 1095. (H, I) Sertularella mixta Galea & Schories, 2012 a. Portion of colony from MHNG-INVE- 79667 (H) and hydrotheca from HRG- 0395 (I). (J-L) Sertularella novarae Marktanner-Turneretscher, 1890. Stem fragment (J), hydrothecae (K), and gonothecae (L) from sample ZMB Cni 944. (M-P) Sertularella oblonga Galea, Häussermann & Försterra, sp. nov. Portions of colony (M, N), hydrothecae (O) and female gonothecae (P). Scale bars: 200 μm (C-E, G, I, K, O), 500 μm (L, P), 1 mm (A, B, F, H, J, M, N)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1024542/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

